# {{projectName}}

A [vinext](https://github.com/your-username/vinext) project scaffolded with
`create-nextion-app`, powered by [`@nextion/core`](https://github.com/your-username/vinext/tree/main/packages/nextion)
on Cloudflare Workers + D1 + R2 + Cloudflare Images.

## Quick start

```bash
pnpm install
cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars       # fill in real values
pnpm dev                              # boots vinext on http://localhost:3001
```

The first run will not have a database. To set one up locally:

```bash
# Create a local D1 database
pnpm exec wrangler d1 create {{projectNameLower}}-db
# Paste the printed `database_id` into both `wrangler.jsonc` and `.dev.vars`.
pnpm exec wrangler d1 migrations apply {{projectNameLower}}-db --local
```

## What's included

- `app/page.tsx` — landing page wired to `siteConfig`
- `app/api/health/route.ts` — `GET /api/health` from nextion
- `app/api/auth/*` — Google OAuth, email verify, viewer endpoints from nextion
- `app/login/page.tsx` — minimal email/password login form
- `lib/auth.config.ts` — `AuthConfig` consumed by `createAuth`
- `lib/admin/nav.ts` — sidebar items for `/admin/*`
- `lib/site/config.ts` — site-level config rendered on the landing page
- `lib/content/models.ts` — one Notion-backed content source: `{{contentSourceId}}`
- `worker/index.ts` — `createNextionWorker` + vinext fallthrough
- `migrations/0001_init.sql` — nextion auth schema (users, app_settings, auth_rate_limits)
- `wrangler.jsonc` — D1 + KV + R2 + Images + Assets bindings

## Tests

```bash
pnpm test
```

The single sanity test under `tests/smoke.test.ts` confirms that
`defineContentSource` registered the `{{contentSourceId}}` source with the
nextion registry and that re-registration is idempotent on `id`.

## Deploy

```bash
pnpm exec wrangler d1 migrations apply {{projectNameLower}}-db --remote
pnpm exec wrangler kv namespace create CONTENT_CACHE
# Paste the printed id into `wrangler.jsonc` under `kv_namespaces[*].id`.
pnpm exec wrangler r2 bucket create {{projectNameLower}}-assets
pnpm exec vinext deploy
```

## Wiring up the nextion package

The dependency is currently `"@nextion/core": "workspace:*"` so this
project can be developed inside the vinext monorepo. **TODO: change to
`"^1.0.0"` before publishing** — the package is published to GitHub Packages
on every merge to `main` (see `.changeset/` and `.github/workflows/release.yml`).

To consume a local build of the package, add to your own `pnpm-workspace.yaml`:

```yaml
packages:
  - "../vinext-monorepo/packages/nextion"
```

Then re-run `pnpm install` so pnpm picks up the local link.
